results.name: Decimal expansion of first zero of BesselJ(2,z).
comment: Also the first root of the sinc(4,x) function, that is, the radial component of the 4D Fourier transform of 4-dimensional unit sphere. Also, the solution of 2J_1(x) = x*J_0(x). - _Stanislav Sykora_, Nov 14 2013
link: Stanislav Sykora, K-Space Images of n-Dimensional Spheres and Generalized Sinc Functions
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Bessel Function Zeros
